# Geopolitical Pattern Intelligence System (GPIS)

Local AI that finds historical patterns in geopolitical events.
Runs 100% offline. No API keys. No cloud. Windows auto-installer.

## What it does

You describe a current geopolitical event. The system:

1. Searches 100,000+ real historical events (GDELT corpus)
2. Finds the closest structural pattern
3. Runs a self-refining loop (3–7 iterations)
4. Searches for counterexamples to its own hypothesis
5. Validates every claim against the corpus
6. Generates a PDF report with charts and confidence scores

## Backtesting results

| Case | Predicted | Actual | Match |
|------|-----------|--------|-------|
| Russia-Ukraine buildup 2021 | ESCALATING | ESCALATING | ✓ |
| US-China trade war 2019 | DE-ESCALATING | DE-ESCALATING | ✓ |
| Brexit aftermath 2016 | VOLATILE | VOLATILE | ✓ |

## Stack

- Local LLM via Ollama (Llama 3.1 8B / Qwen2.5 1.5B)
- ChromaDB vector store
- LangGraph agentic loop
- GDELT 2.0 corpus pipeline
- FastAPI + React dashboard
- ReportLab + Matplotlib PDF reports

## Hardware requirements

| Tier | RAM | Model | Analysis time |
|------|-----|-------|---------------|
| 1 | 2GB | Qwen2.5 1.5B | ~10 min |
| 2 | 6GB | Llama 3.1 8B | ~20 min |
| 3 | 12GB | Llama 3.1 8B | ~30 min |

## Installation

Double-click `install.bat` — installs everything automatically.
No terminal. No configuration. No technical knowledge required.

